        <p>If you are working with a source control application other than those directly supported in <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> (i.e., <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare,Products.Analyzer"><MadCap:keyword term="Source control:Microsoft Visual SourceSafe;Microsoft Visual SourceSafe" />Microsoft Visual SourceSafe, </MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:keyword term="Source control:Microsoft Team Foundation Server;Microsoft Team Foundation Server" />Microsoft Team Foundation Server, <MadCap:keyword term="Perforce;Source control:Perforce" />Perforce, <MadCap:keyword term="Apache Subversion;Source control:Subversion" />Apache Subversion, <MadCap:keyword term="Source control:Git;Git" />Git), you can use the Microsoft Source Code Control API (SCC API) to integrate that application with your <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> project. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2,Products.FlareOnlineOnly,Products.LingoOnlineOnly">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Source_Control/Third_Party_Plug_Ins/Using_an_API_to_Integrate_Source_Control.htm">Using an API to Integrate Source Control</MadCap:xref>. </MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:snippetText src="../ForMoreInfo/SeeFlareOnlineHelp.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer" /></p>
